OL,3,CBoy, 14, becomes 11th person to die in
OL,4,Cwater during record heatwave
OL,6,FA 14-year-old has become the 11th
OL,7,Fperson to die after getting into
OL,8,Fdifficulty in open water during the
OL,9,Frecord-breaking May heatwave.
OL,11,FNine children and two adults have now
OL,12,Fdied in open water incidents over the
OL,13,Fpast week as temperatures soared to
OL,14,Fabove 30C in parts of the country.
OL,16,FIn the latest incident, Thames Valley
OL,17,FPolice confirmed on Thursday that the
OL,18,Fboy died "after getting into
OL,19,Fdifficulty in the River Thames at
OL,20,FDonnington Bridge" on May 27.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/12
