OL,3,CBoy, 14, becomes 11th person to die in
OL,4,Cwater during record heatwave
OL,6,FThe boy's death is not being treated
OL,7,Fas suspicious at this time, Kent
OL,8,FPolice said.
OL,10,FSo far, those reported to have died in
OL,11,Fwater incidents are:
OL,13,FOther bodies found include 12-year-old
OL,14,FJunior Slater, from Clayton-le-Woods,
OL,15,Fwho died in the River Ribble, in North
OL,16,FYorkshire, on Tuesday after getting
OL,17,Finto difficulty while swimming with
OL,18,Ffriends.
OL,20,FIn a statement, his family paid
OL,21,Ftribute to "our little blue-eyed boy".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
